Senior administration officials held a background briefing to discuss efforts to address global transportation supply chain bottlenecks. They highlighted the strong economic recovery in the U.S. due to the President's Rescue Plan and measures to combat COVID-19. However, they acknowledged that supply chains have been disrupted due to increased demand and global challenges caused by the pandemic. They emphasized the need for a 24/7 operation in the supply chain and announced commitments from major companies like Walmart, FedEx, and UPS to move towards 24/7 operations. The officials also discussed the importance of improving infrastructure and capacity in ports, rail, and roads to accommodate the growing volume of goods. They mentioned ongoing efforts to address labor shortages in the trucking industry and encouraged all stakeholders to work together to alleviate bottlenecks in the supply chain.